The article is a message from the White House to Congress, regarding the ATOMAL Agreement with Croatia. The agreement, which authorizes the exchange of U.S. Restricted Data and Formerly Restricted Data within the context of NATO, has been signed by Croatia and meets the requirements of the Atomic Energy Act of 1954. The agreement has been in force since 1965 with other NATO members, and the inclusion of Croatia will enhance the cohesiveness and effectiveness of the Alliance. The Department of Defense and other agencies have reviewed and recommended the agreement, and it is deemed to promote the common defense and security without constituting an unreasonable risk. The approval of the agreement begins a 60-day continuous session period for Congress to review it.